<h2>Current work</h2>
<p>I am currently a Software Engineeer for <a href="http://basho.com">Basho Technologies</a>. I work on <a href="http://docs.basho.com">Riak&#8217;s</a> server- and client-side code. I work daily in Erlang, Ruby, Python, and occasionally in other languages.</p>
<ul>
	<li><a href="https://github.com/seancribbs/webmachine-ruby">Webmachine-Ruby</a>, a toolkit that helps you write well-behaved <span class="caps">HTTP</span> applications in Ruby, a port of the original <a href="https://github.com/basho/webmachine">Erlang version</a>.</li>
	<li><a href="https://github.com/seancribbs/neotoma">neotoma</a> is a parser-generator for parsing expression grammars that generates Packrat-style parsers in Erlang.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Past consulting projects</h2>
<ul>
	<li><a href="http://www.myschoolbinder.com">Schoolbinder</a>, a goal-tracking application for teachers and students (<a href="http://demo.myschoolbinder.com">demo</a> &#8211; <code>teacher@myschoolbinder.com</code> / <code>teacher</code>)</li>
	<li>Enhancements to <a href="http://diopa.net">diopa.net</a> in collaboration with <a href="http://spurrd.com">Paul du Coudray</a>.</li>
	<li>A redesign of <a href="http://www.mexconnect.com">MexConnect</a>, the leading and oldest portal for information about Mexico, in collaboration with <a href="http://hellovenado.com">Loren Johnson</a> and <a href="http://spurrd.com">Paul du Coudray</a>. (Mar &#8217;09)</li>
	<li>A migration of <a href="http://www.con-way.com">www.con-way.com</a> from a custom <span class="caps">CMS</span> to Radiant (Oct &#8217;08)</li>
	<li>The new <a href="http://redken.com">Redken</a> <a href="http://redkensalon.com">sites</a>, built on Radiant <span class="caps">CMS</span> in collaboration with <a href="http://digitalpulp.com">Digital Pulp</a>. (Feb &#8217;08)</li>
</ul>
